bs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"WordPress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"WordSesh\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:32:\"http://webdevstudios.com/?p=8834\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:712:\"<p>It&#8217;s that time of year again &#8212; WordSesh is back for its third year! This year it is being held on Saturday, December 20th from 00:00 &#8211; 24:00 UTC. Not sure how to coordinate UTC time with your time zone? Don&#8217;t worry &#8212; check with Worldtimeserver.com if you ... <a class=\"moretag button orange\" href=\"http://webdevstudios.com/2014/12/15/wordsesh-3-24-hours-of-wordpress-presentations/\">Read More</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://webdevstudios.com/2014/12/15/wordsesh-3-24-hours-of-wordpress-presentations/\">WordSesh 3 &#8211; 24 Hours of WordPress Presentations</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://webdevstudios.com\">WebDevStudios.com</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Melissa Hoppe\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:3350:\"<p>It&#8217;s that time of year again &#8212; <a href=\"http://wordsesh.org/\">WordSesh</a> is back for its <strong>third</strong> year! This year it is being held on Saturday, December 20th from 00:00 &#8211; 24:00 UTC. Not sure how to coordinate UTC time with your time zone? Don&#8217;t worry &#8212; check with <a href=\"http://www.worldtimeserver.com/current_time_in_UTC.aspx\">Worldtimeserver.com </a>if you get jumbled.</p>\n<h2>What is WordSesh?<img class=\"alignright size-thumbnail wp-image-8837\" src=\"https://webdevstudios.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/Rrz4Wdf9-150x150.png\" alt=\"Rrz4Wdf9\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></h2>\n<p>WordSesh is a 1 full day (24 hours) event of WordPress presentations from the awesome people of the WordPress community. 1 presentation, every hour, on the hour.</p>\n<h2>What are the perks of WordSesh?</h2>\n<p>Well, for one thing, it&#8217;s completely <strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">FREE</span></strong>! You read that right &#8212; 24 hours of WordPress presentations from some of the smartest people around the world, for free. Not to mention, it&#8217;s all in the comfort of your own home. You get to jam pack your brain with knowledge while you&#8217;re in your PJ&#8217;s and you don&#8217;t even have to reach for your wallet. Grab some hot coco (with marshmallows!) and get cozy!<span id=\"more-10187\"></span></p>\n<h2>Who? Where? When?</h2>\n<p><a href=\"http://3oil7x2swx3d30yjgq23wmyu.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/s7fimjrn.png\" rel=\"lightbox[10187]\"><img class=\"alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-8838\" src=\"https://webdevstudios.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/s7fimjrn-150x150.png\" alt=\"s7fimjrn\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></a>Keeping up with tradition &#8212; <a title=\"Brad Williams\" href=\"http://webdevstudios.com/team/brad-williams/\">Brad Williams</a> and <a title=\"Dre Armeda\" href=\"http://webdevstudios.com/team/dre-armeda/\">Dre Armeda</a> are kicking off the event at <strong>0:00 UTC</strong> with <a href=\"http://dradcast.com/\">DradCast</a> along with WordSesh organizer, <a href=\"https://twitter.com/scottbasgaard\">Scott Basgaard</a>!</p>\n<p>You can also catch Brad and Dre later on during WordSesh at <strong>23:00 UTC</strong> on the WordPress News Round Table.</p>\n<p><a title=\"Lisa Sabin-Wilson\" href=\"http://webdevstudios.com/team/lisa-sabin-wilson/\">Lisa Sabin-Wilson</a> is on the roster of speakers, too! You can tune into her talk at <strong>19:00 UTC</strong>. She will be presenting to you about <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Conducting A Thorough Theme Review.</span></p>\n<p>As a group of people who are extremely passionate about WordPress and the community that has been built around it &#8212; We are excited and honored to be a part of WordSesh for the third year running!</p>\n<p>To keep up with WordSesh updates; you can follow the event on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/WordSesh\">Twitter</a> and use the <a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/WordSesh?src=hash\">#WordSesh</a> hashtag to talk with others about your experiences during the event.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://webdevstudios.com/2014/12/15/wordsesh-3-24-hours-of-wordpress-presentations/\">WordSesh 3 &#8211; 24 Hours of WordPress Presentations</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://webdevstudios.com\">WebDevStudios.com</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:88:\"http://webdevstudios.com/2014/12/15/wordsesh-3-24-hours-of-wordpress-presentations/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:45:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:17:\"Viva La WordCamp!\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:53:\"http://webdevstudios.com/2014/12/12/viva-la-wordcamp/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:62:\"http://webdevstudios.com/2014/12/12/viva-la-wordcamp/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Fri, 12 Dec 2014 16:11:08 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"Team\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"WordCamp\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:32:\"http://webdevstudios.com/?p=8825\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:634:\"<p>It&#8217;s time for WordCamp Las Vegas! It is being held this year from Saturday, December 13th until Sunday, December 14th at the Innevation Center. This WordCamp offers two different tracks &#8212; Developer/Designer and User/Business. On Sunday, there will also be a workshop that you can attend. Both ... <a class=\"moretag button orange\" href=\"http://webdevstudios.com/2014/12/12/viva-la-wordcamp/\">Read More</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://webdevstudios.com/2014/12/12/viva-la-wordcamp/\">Viva La WordCamp!</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://webdevstudios.com\">WebDevStudios.com</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Melissa Hoppe\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:3713:\"<p><a href=\"http://3oil7x2swx3d30yjgq23wmyu.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/WordCamp-Las-Vegas-20141.png\" rel=\"lightbox[10186]\"><img class=\" size-medium wp-image-8827 alignright\" src=\"https://webdevstudios.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/WordCamp-Las-Vegas-20141-281x300.png\" alt=\"WordCamp Las Vegas 2014\" width=\"281\" height=\"300\" /></a>It&#8217;s time for <a href=\"http://2014.vegas.wordcamp.org/\">WordCamp Las Vegas</a>! It is being held this year from Saturday, December 13th until Sunday, December 14th at the Innevation Center. This WordCamp offers two different tracks &#8212; Developer/Designer and User/Business. On Sunday, there will also be a workshop that you can attend. Both <a title=\"Dre Armeda\" href=\"http://webdevstudios.com/team/dre-armeda/\">Dre Armeda</a> and <a title=\"Suzette Franck\" href=\"http://webdevstudios.com/team/suzette-franck/\">Suzette Franck</a> of WebDevStudios will be attending and speaking at this event!</p>\n<p>You&#8217;ll be able to catch Dre on Saturday, the 13th in the Developer/Designer track at 10 AM alongside <a href=\"http://9seeds.com/\">9Seeds</a> owner, <a href=\"https://twitter.com/vegasgeek\">John Hawkins</a>. You have the opportunity to hear them talk to you about <em>Business Principles for WordPress Project Success</em>.<span id=\"more-10186\"></span></p>\n<p>Here&#8217;s a short description of what you&#8217;ll hear about &#8212;</p>\n<blockquote><p>In this session Dre and John will talk about key areas they like to focus on that lead to successful projects. The two well known and respected WordPress entrepreneurs will share with you several of the things they’ve learned along the way. Hopefully one or two of them will save you from having to learn the same lessons at the school of hard knocks.</p>\n<hr />\n</blockquote>\n<p>You will also get the chance to see Suzette during the Sunday Workshop at 2:30 PM. She&#8217;s going to present to you about the <em>Ten Features of Jetpack You Can&#8217;t Live Without.</em></p>\n<p>Here&#8217;s a short description of what you&#8217;ll hear about &#8212;</p>\n<blockquote><p>Since its inception from WordPress.com Stats several years ago, the Jetpack suite of plugins has matured into a well-rounded group of helpful tools that you’ll wonder how you could ever live without. A must for any self-hosted WordPress site owner, this session will cover how to leverage the top ten most useful social media features and the WordPress.com cloud-powered awesomeness to collect stats and provide feedback, such as the contact form, related posts, the top posts and pages widget, and more.</p>\n<p>This 75 minute hands-on presentation with Q &amp; A will cover the basics of how to get started with and how to use some of the awesome modules that come with Jetpack. Jetpack requires a WordPress.org account and a publicly accessible WordPress website, which will be necessary to participate in the class lessons. Others will be encouraged to ask questions and take notes for later.</p></blockquote>\n<p>If you don&#8217;t have the opportunity to see Dre or Suzette&#8217;s presentations; You can find them around the venue or on twitter. Use the hashtag #WCLV14 and attach <a href=\"https://twitter.com/dremeda\">Dre</a> or <a href=\"https://twitter.com/suzette_franck\">Suzette&#8217;s</a> twitter handle and you&#8217;ll be sure to catch their attention!</p>\n<p>As always, Dre and Suzette are excited to share their knowledge and connect with people who love what they love &#8212; WordPress!</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://webdevstudios.com/2014/12/12/viva-la-wordcamp/\">Viva La WordCamp!</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://webdevstudios.com\">WebDevStudios.com</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:58:\"http://webdevstudios.com/2014/12/12/viva-la-wordcamp/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:57:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:32:\"WDS Holiday Charity Competition!\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:68:\"http://webdevstudios.com/2014/12/08/wds-holiday-charity-competition/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:77:\"http://webdevstudios.com/2014/12/08/wds-holiday-charity-competition/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 08 Dec 2014 19:30:24 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:6:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Community\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"Team\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"Charity\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Code For Kids\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:3:\"EFF\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"Uganda\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:32:\"http://webdevstudios.com/?p=8810\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:623:\"<p>With the holidays fast approaching, our team at WebDevStudios wanted to do something special that got everyone on our team into the holiday spirit, and into the spirit of giving! Each of our teams at WDS has chosen a charity that they cared about and ... <a class=\"moretag button orange\" href=\"http://webdevstudios.com/2014/12/08/wds-holiday-charity-competition/\">Read More</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://webdevstudios.com/2014/12/08/wds-holiday-charity-competition/\">WDS Holiday Charity Competition!</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://webdevstudios.com\">WebDevStudios.com</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Melissa Hoppe\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8653:\"<p><a href=\"http://3oil7x2swx3d30yjgq23wmyu.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/holiday-charity.png\" rel=\"lightbox[9540]\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-9558\" src=\"http://3oil7x2swx3d30yjgq23wmyu.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/holiday-charity.png\" alt=\"holiday-charity\" width=\"800\" height=\"303\" /></a></p>\n<p>With the holidays fast approaching, our team at WebDevStudios wanted to do something special that got everyone on our team into the holiday spirit, and into the spirit of giving! Each of our teams at WDS has chosen a charity that they cared about and have put their own creative twist on their charitable efforts by turning it into a competition, of sorts, between teams.  Instead of WDS donating to one charity as a whole, we&#8217;ve made it into a competition between the three teams that make up our amazing group. As for the team that raises the most money? WebDevStudios is contributing $1000.00 to the winning team&#8217;s charity!</p>\n<hr />\n<p>We have<strong> &#8220;The A-Team&#8221;</strong> which consists of &#8212; <a title=\"Jaimie Olmstead\" href=\"http://webdevstudios.com/team/jaimie-olmstead/\">Jaimie Olmstead</a>, <a title=\"Ben Lobaugh\" href=\"http://webdevstudios.com/team/ben-lobaugh/\">Ben Lobaugh</a>, <a title=\"Greg Rickaby\" href=\"http://webdevstudios.com/team/greg-rickaby/\">Greg Rickaby</a>, <a title=\"Camden Segal\" href=\"http://webdevstudios.com/team/camden-segal/\">Camden Segal</a>, <a title=\"Damon Cook\" href=\"http://webdevstudios.com/team/damon-cook/\">Damon Cook</a>, <a title=\"Dustin Filippini\" href=\"http://webdevstudios.com/team/dustin-filippini/\">Dustin Filippini</a>, <a title=\"Ryan Fugate\" href=\"http://webdevstudios.com/team/ryan-fugate/\">Ryan Fugate</a>, <a title=\"Simon Urbina\" href=\"http://webdevstudios.com/team/simon-urbina/\">Simon Urbina</a>, <a title=\"Chris Reynolds\" href=\"http://webdevstudios.com/team/chris-reynolds/\">Chris Reynolds</a>, <a title=\"Michael Beckwith\" href=\"http://webdevstudios.com/team/michael-beckwith/\">Michael Beckwith</a>, and <a title=\"Melissa Hoppe\" href=\"http://webdevstudios.com/team/melissa-hoppe/\">Melissa Hoppe</a>.</p>\n<p>This team has chosen the <a href=\"http://freedomprojectz.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Freedom Projectz</a> to gather donations for.</p>\n<p><strong>Freedom Projectz</strong> is a charity focused on Ugandan youth. It&#8217;s devoted to empowering orphaned students to become leaders in their country through higher education, vocational training, and community service. Their goal is to help the students become self-sustaining within five years and break the cycle of poverty through using their professional careers to help others.<span id=\"more-9540\"></span></p>\n<blockquote>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">      Hope. Empower. Sustain.</h2>\n</blockquote>\n<p><a href=\"http://3oil7x2swx3d30yjgq23wmyu.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/a3414e9b-7efd-49a2-b682-88dce8ee24d2_profile.jpg\" rel=\"lightbox[9540]\"><img class=\"alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-8811\" src=\"https://webdevstudios.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/a3414e9b-7efd-49a2-b682-88dce8ee24d2_profile-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"a3414e9b-7efd-49a2-b682-88dce8ee24d2_profile\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></a>The organization has a special place in the A-team&#8217;s heart. Developer lead, Ben Lobaugh has spent many of his own hours helping this cause. With your donations, we hope to be able to provide these youth with more opportunities specifically to explore and experience technology.</p>\n<h2><a href=\"http://www.youcaring.com/nonprofits/help-the-youth-of-uganda-with-wds/273621\" target=\"_blank\">DONATE TO THIS CAUSE!</a></h2>\n<hr />\n<p>Next up is <strong>&#8220;Scream Team&#8221;</strong> which consists of &#8212; <a title=\"Cristina Cannon\" href=\"http://webdevstudios.com/team/cristina-cannon/\">Cristina Cannon</a>, <a title=\"Justin Sternberg\" href=\"http://webdevstudios.com/team/justin-sternberg/\">Justin Sternberg</a>, <a title=\"Corey Collins\" href=\"http://webdevstudios.com/team/corey-collins/\">Corey Collins</a>, <a title=\"Jay Wood\" href=\"http://webdevstudios.com/team/jay-wood/\">Jay Wood</a>, <a title=\"Marcus Battle\" href=\"http://webdevstudios.com/team/marcus-battle/\">Marcus Battle</a>, <a title=\"Brad Parbs\" href=\"http://webdevstudios.com/team/brad-parbs/\">Brad Parbs</a>, <a title=\"Will Schmierer\" href=\"http://webdevstudios.com/team/will-schmierer/\">Will Schmierer</a>, <a title=\"Suzette Franck\" href=\"http://webdevstudios.com/team/suzette-franck/\">Suzette Franck</a>, <a title=\"Matt McAchran\" href=\"http://webdevstudios.com/team/matt-mcachran/\">Matt McAchran</a>, <a title=\"Nate Schaumburg\" href=\"http://webdevstudios.com/team/nate-schaumburg/\">Nate Schaumburg</a>, and <a title=\"April Williams\" href=\"http://webdevstudios.com/team/april-heline/\">April Williams</a>.</p>\n<p>This team chose the <a href=\"https://codestarter.org/\">CodeStarter </a>organization to gather donations for.</p>\n<p>There are many children across the country that want to learn to code, but do not have the proper tools to do so. Codestarter.org is an awesome non-profit that uses your donations to give free computers to children enrolled in programming classes with one of their partner organizations.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">It all starts with a computer.</h2>\n</blockquote>\n<p>At Codestarter, they strive to ensure that every child <img class=\"alignright size-thumbnail wp-image-8812\" src=\"https://webdevstudios.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/99e421a1-a7fc-48eb-a0f5-70ccebe65475_profile-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"99e421a1-a7fc-48eb-a0f5-70ccebe65475_profile\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" />has the opportunity to learn how to code. WebDevStudios also believes that it starts with having a computer to do so. We hope to raise money to help the Codestarter cause and get more kids involved in the coding and WordPress community.</p>\n<h2><a href=\"http://www.youcaring.com/other/help-wds-give-the-gift-of-code-to-kids-across-the-globe/273593\" target=\"_blank\">DONATE TO THIS CAUSE!</a></h2>\n<hr />\n<p>And last, but certainly not least; we have <strong>&#8220;Team Maintainn&#8221;</strong> which consists of &#8212; <a title=\"Shayne Sanderson\" href=\"http://webdevstudios.com/team/shayne-sanderson/\">Shayne Sanderson</a>, <a title=\"Patrick Garman\" href=\"http://webdevstudios.com/team/patrick-garman/\">Patrick Garman</a>, <a title=\"George Mamadashvili\" href=\"http://webdevstudios.com/team/george-mamadashvili/\">George Mamadashvili</a>, and <a title=\"Rami Abraham\" href=\"http://webdevstudios.com/team/rami-abraham/\">Rami Abraham</a>.</p>\n<p>They have chosen the <a href=\"https://www.eff.org/\">Electronic Frontier Foundation</a> to gather donations for.</p>\n<p>Founded in 1990, EFF champions user privacy, free expression, and innovation through impact litigation, policy analysis, grassroots activism, and technology development. We work to ensure that rights and freedoms are enhanced and protected as our use of technology grows.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">Defending your rights in the digital world.</h2>\n</blockquote>\n<div class=\"blob-wrapper data type-html js-blob-data\">\n<p class=\"file-data\"><a href=\"http://3oil7x2swx3d30yjgq23wmyu.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/eff-logo-plain-black-300.jpg\" rel=\"lightbox[9540]\"><img class=\"alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-8813\" src=\"https://webdevstudios.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/eff-logo-plain-black-300-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"eff-logo-plain-black-300\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></a>Team Maintainn chose the EFF as their charity because of its&#8217; impact in twenty-first century life. One of its&#8217; primary goals &#8211; that of maintaining net neutrality &#8211; affects every other charity as well; where smaller voices on the Internet are silenced by the Draconian Internet traffic policy, they&#8217;d suffer as well.</p>\n<h2 class=\"file-data\"><a href=\"http://www.youcaring.com/nonprofits/help-us-maintainn-net-neutrality/274798\" target=\"_blank\">DONATE TO THIS CAUSE!</a></h2>\n</div>\n<hr />\n<p>Although this is a competition between the teams; the end goal is simple &#8212; to contribute to these three great causes that we at WebDevStudios are passionate about. We are finishing up the donations on <strong>December 24th, 2014 at 12:00 PM EST</strong>.</p>\n<p>Please spread the word on social media and donate to one or all three of the causes &#8212; every little bit helps!</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://webdevstudios.com/2014/12/08/wds-holiday-charity-competition/\">WDS Holiday Charity Competition!</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://webdevstudios.com\">WebDevStudios.com</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:73:\"http://webdevstudios.com/2014/12/08/wds-holiday-charity-competition/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"2\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:45:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:75:\"Customizing the WordPress Dashboard by Creating a Simple Admin Theme Plugin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:108:\"http://webdevstudios.com/2014/12/05/customizing-wordpress-dashboard-by-creating-a-simple-admin-theme-plugin/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:117:\"http://webdevstudios.com/2014/12/05/customizing-wordpress-dashboard-by-creating-a-simple-admin-theme-plugin/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Fri, 05 Dec 2014 19:22:17 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"Plugins\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"Tutorial\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:32:\"http://webdevstudios.com/?p=8790\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:733:\"<p>In this post, you’re going to learn how to create a simple Admin Theme for WordPress. An Admin Theme can be used to create your own color scheme for the WordPress Dashboard or make minor tweaks to the theme that is set in your profile. ... <a class=\"moretag button orange\" href=\"http://webdevstudios.com/2014/12/05/customizing-wordpress-dashboard-by-creating-a-simple-admin-theme-plugin/\">Read More</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://webdevstudios.com/2014/12/05/customizing-wordpress-dashboard-by-creating-a-simple-admin-theme-plugin/\">Customizing the WordPress Dashboard by Creating a Simple Admin Theme Plugin</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://webdevstudios.com\">WebDevStudios.com</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"Nate Schaumburg\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6441:\"<p>In this post, you’re going to learn how to create a simple Admin Theme for WordPress. An Admin Theme can be used to create your own color scheme for the WordPress Dashboard or make minor tweaks to the theme that is set in your profile.</p>\n<p>While the overall default admin theme is slick, there might be few items that you would like to adjust. For example: the font size, link color, background colors, etc. Here are some items that you will be adjusting with your plugin:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Remove box shadow on links and input fields.</li>\n<li>If you like your Dashboard Home to be clear of all screen options, there are still dashed borders showing where the screen options would go. We’re going to remove those.</li>\n<li>Fill in your adjustments: ______________________________</li>\n</ul>\n<p>To make these adjustments, we’re going to follow the official guide that is already available in the <a href=\"http://codex.wordpress.org/Creating_Admin_Themes#Creating_an_Admin_Theme_Plugin\">WordPress Codex</a> on how to create an Admin Theme.<span id=\"more-9539\"></span></p>\n<p>To start off, create a new folder for your plugin and name it &#8216;simple-admin-theme&#8217; or whatever name you choose. Open your favorite text editor and create a new file called &#8216;simple-admin-theme.php&#8217;. In this file, you’ll want to paste the following code:</p>\n<pre class=\"prettyprint lang-php\" title=\"admin theme plugin setup\">&lt;?php\n\n/*\nPlugin Name: Simple Admin Theme\nPlugin URI: https://gist.github.com/precode/9ca75a69fe91671b6266\nDescription: A Simple Admin Theme for WordPress\nAuthor: Precode\nVersion: 1.0.0\nAuthor URI: http://precode.io\n*/\n\nfunction sat_enqueue_custom_admin_theme() {\n    wp_enqueue_style( \'sat-enqueue-custom-admin-theme\', plugins_url( \'wp-admin.css\', __FILE__ ) );\n}\nadd_action( \'admin_enqueue_scripts\', \'sat_enqueue_custom_admin_theme\' );</pre>\n<p>The function that you pasted into your file will properly enqueue your stylesheet that we will be using to add our custom styles for the Admin Theme. Save this file into your &#8216;simple-admin-theme&#8217; folder.</p>\n<p>While still in your editor, you’ll want to create a new file and save it as &#8216;wp-admin.css&#8217; into the same folder as your PHP file.</p>\n<p>Assuming you have WordPress installed, you can now add your admin theme plugin to your WordPress installation under &#8216;wp-content/plugins&#8217;. In your WordPress Dashboard, go to Plugins and you should now see your newly created plugin.</p>\n<p>Now the fun part begins. Re-open your &#8216;wp-admin.css&#8217; file in your text editor. We’re going to keep this stylesheet simple because you are only making minor tweaks to the default Admin theme.</p>\n<p>The first item we will be adjusting are the links. We will still keep the same color, but we’re removing the box shadow when clicking a link in the WordPress Dashboard.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-8796\" src=\"https://webdevstudios.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/adminthemelinks.gif\" alt=\"adminthemelinks\" /></p>\n<p>To do this, copy and paste the following and save:</p>\n<pre class=\"prettyprint lang-cs\" title=\"admin theme css links\">a:focus {\n    -webkit-box-shadow: none;\n    box-shadow: none;\n}</pre>\n<p>After adding the above styles, go back to your WordPress Dashboard and refresh the page. You’ll notice that the box shadow on focus for all links has now been removed. Back in your stylesheet, add the following:</p>\n<pre class=\"prettyprint lang-cs\" title=\"admin theme css inputs\">input[type=&quot;text&quot;]:focus,\ninput[type=&quot;password&quot;]:focus,\ninput[type=&quot;color&quot;]:focus,\ninput[type=&quot;date&quot;]:focus,\ninput[type=&quot;datetime&quot;]:focus,\ninput[type=&quot;datetime-local&quot;]:focus,\ninput[type=&quot;email&quot;]:focus,\ninput[type=&quot;month&quot;]:focus,\ninput[type=&quot;number&quot;]:focus,\ninput[type=&quot;password&quot;]:focus,\ninput[type=&quot;search&quot;]:focus,\ninput[type=&quot;tel&quot;]:focus,\ninput[type=&quot;text&quot;]:focus,\ninput[type=&quot;time&quot;]:focus,\ninput[type=&quot;url&quot;]:focus,\ninput[type=&quot;week&quot;]:focus,\ninput[type=&quot;checkbox&quot;]:focus,\ninput[type=&quot;radio&quot;]:focus,\nselect:focus,\ntextarea:focus {\n    -webkit-box-shadow: none;\n    box-shadow: none;\n}</pre>\n<p>This will update all input fields on focus so no box shadow will appear. Next on our list is to remove all screen options on your Dashboard Homepage. Click the ‘Dashboard’ link in your WordPress admin. Click the Screen Options button at the top right of the page and uncheck all options. We are now going to add the following to your stylesheet to remove the dashed border that indicates where the screen options will appear:</p>\n<pre class=\"prettyprint lang-cs\" title=\"admin theme css remove border\">.metabox-holder .postbox-container .empty-container {\n    border: none;\n}</pre>\n<p>Save your stylesheet and reload the WordPress Dashboard. You’ll see that the dashed borders have been removed.</p>\n<p>From there, you can add your own adjustments by right clicking elements in your browser and click &#8216;Inspect Element&#8217; to get the property name and styles to edit from your browsers’ web inspector.</p>\n<p>You have now created your first Admin Theme; essentially, your first WordPress plugin if you have not developed one before! If you like, you can add your new plugin to your GitHub profile for others to build on and or submit it to the <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/add/\">WordPress plugin repository</a>. When adding any changes to the default WordPress Admin theme that you might think are actual issues, you can submit a ticket to <a href=\"https://core.trac.wordpress.org/\">WordPress Trac</a> and provide a patch to fix the possible issue. If you do not know how to contribute to WordPress, we have a <a href=\"http://webdevstudios.com/2014/11/14/beginners-guide-to-contributing-to-wordpress/\">great post</a> for you to read.</p>\n<p>If you like this post, be sure to follow us on Twitter <a href=\"https://twitter.com/webdevstudios\">@webdevstudios</a> for new tutorials and tips.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://webdevstudios.com/2014/12/05/customizing-wordpress-dashboard-by-creating-a-simple-admin-theme-plugin/\">Customizing the WordPress Dashboard by Creating a Simple Admin Theme Plugin</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://webdevstudios.com\">WebDevStudios.com</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:113:\"http://webdevstudios.com/2014/12/05/customizing-wordpress-dashboard-by-creating-a-simple-admin-theme-plugin/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}}}s:2