(517,	1,	'2015-01-09 08:22:33',	'2015-01-09 08:22:33',	'Dr. Nguyen Huu Le has been working in the IT/Telecom fields for more than 40 years in Australia, Canada, U.K., Japan, and has been a pioneer in the development of the software industry in Vietnam. He spent 22 years with Nortel, and was mostly involved in the R&amp;D Globalization and Externalization programs where one of his most important contributions was the recognition and utilization of the skilled human resources from the Asia Pacific region, including Japan, China, Vietnam, and India. He left Nortel as the Director of Global R&amp;D Planning in 2000 to become the President and CEO of Paragon Asia Pacific, managing their development centers in Vietnam and India. Since joining TMA at the end of 2001, he serves also as the Chief Marketing Officer to promote TMA to the world, and as the Chief Mentor, to help build the foundation for the company based on the best practices in the industry.',	'Le Nguyen-Huu test',	'',	'inherit',	'open',	'open',	'',	'436-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2015-01-09 08:22:33',	'2015-01-09 08:22:33',	'',	436,	'https://nhunguyen-nhunguyen1980.c9.io/Vnito/2015/01/436-revision-v1/',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
