(648,	1,	'2015-01-10 16:50:46',	'2015-01-10 16:50:46',	'<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class=\"left-col\">Name</td>\r\n<td>Nguyen Cong Ai</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class=\"left-col\">Position</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Partner – Ho Chi Minh Office, Tax &amp; Corporate Services</li>\r\n	<li>Head of Market Entry Group</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class=\"left-col\">Qualifications</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>PhD in International Business, University of Economics, Bratislava, Slovak Republic</li>\r\n	<li>MA in International Economics</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class=\"left-col\">Experiences</td>\r\n<td>PhD Nguyen Cong Ai has been working for KPMG since 1998, in Slovakia and Vietnam. He has been involved in providing Market Entry advisory services to many international companies entering Vietnam.. PhD Nguyen Cong Ai has extensive experience in conducting market entry studies, location analysis, commercial due diligence and assistance with Investment licensing and post-license compliance.Being in contact with Government Agencies and Business Communities throughout Vietnam for years, Ai has extensive business and government network.Dr Ai’s clients include many of leading companies in Vietnam and overseas: Petro Vietnam Fertilizer and Chemicals Company, Kookmin Bank, Lotte Mart, Masan Group Corporation, Vietnam Southern Food General Corporation, Mitsubishi Corporation, Deutsche Bank AG, Sharp Corporation.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>',	'Ai Nguyen-Cong',	'',	'inherit',	'open',	'open',	'',	'415-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2015-01-10 16:50:46',	'2015-01-10 16:50:46',	'',	415,	'https://nhunguyen-nhunguyen1980.c9.io/Vnito/2015/01/415-revision-v1/',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
(651,	1,	'2015-01-10 16:52:33',	'2015-01-10 16:52:33',	'Vu Lam is the CEO and Founder of KMS. He owns the vision and global delivery operations for KMS. He was one of the co-founders of KMS with the belief that there should be a better way to provide software outsourcing, for his clients as well as for the engineers. He was confident that he knew the way, so he started the journey of KMS with his partners to prove it. To be successful, Vu knows that he needs to recognize the talent and strengths of the team, and allow them to utilize it to achieve success for themselves and for KMS clients.\r\n\r\nVu co-founded Paragon Solutions, Inc., a US-based technology consulting company with international development centers in Bangalore, India and Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam. His establishment and guidance of Paragon Solutions Vietnam (PSV) led to his recognition as a pioneer of the Vietnam IT industry. Following the acquisition of Paragon by First Consulting Group (FCG), a NASDAQ traded company, Vu led FCG\'s Global Shared-Services group and led the growth of the organization from 400 to 1,300+ resources. Vu is also currently a Board member of several IT startup companies.',	'Lam Vu-Quoc',	'',	'inherit',	'open',	'open',	'',	'368-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2015-01-10 16:52:33',	'2015-01-10 16:52:33',	'',	368,	'https://nhunguyen-nhunguyen1980.c9.io/Vnito/2015/01/368-revision-v1/',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
