(780,	5,	'2015-01-14 10:55:01',	'2015-01-14 10:55:01',	'Mr. Long Vuong has been working for LogiGear for 6 years as Head of HR. While helping the Company acquiring and growing a quality and scalable workforce, now at 800 headcounts, he has been actively participating in IT/software community when representing LogiGear to HCA, QTSC, VINASA, AMCHAM, and SE/CS schools in HCMC and Danang, Vietnam. He was a member of the Organizing Board for VISTACON (Vietnam International Software Testing &amp; Automation Conference) for 2010, 2011, 2013, hosted by LogiGear &amp; HCA (2013).\r\n\r\nInterestingly, although Mr. Vuong is serving in human resources, his solid background is Finance &amp; Accounting with more than 20 years experience. Aside from that, he makes his hobby as a free-lance translator/editor with a proud “fortune” of more than 30 books published in Vietnamese, such as The Snowball, Classic Drucker, Differentiate or Die, The 7 Habits of Highly Effective People, The 8th Habit, The Speed of Trust, The Principle-Centered Leadership, Break-through Thinking, Think &amp; Grow Rich, Nudge, The 24-Carrot Manager, etc.',	'Long Vuong-Bao',	'',	'inherit',	'open',	'open',	'',	'559-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2015-01-14 10:55:01',	'2015-01-14 10:55:01',	'',	559,	'https://nhunguyen-nhunguyen1980.c9.io/Vnito/559-revision-v1/',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
(781,	5,	'2015-01-14 10:56:11',	'2015-01-14 10:56:11',	'Mr. Long Lam-Nguyen-Hai (Long Lam) worked as Deputy CEO of Quang Trung Software City (QTSC) which was the biggest information technology park in Vietnam (www.qtsc.com.vn). Prior this role, he led as Project Director, CMO and Head of Business Support Center and Public Relations. Long also charged Vice Chairman of ICT Partnerships Club - the ICT businessmen club in Vietnam with over 80 members.\r\nAs an information technology industry expert, he was a President of the Asia Oceania Regional Software Park Alliance in the term 2010-2012, a member of consultant board to support Vietnam Software Business Incubator design the business plan and strategy for development in order to report to Vietnamese Government and European Commission. Furthermore, he contributed positively to VNCI project (www.vnci.org) funded by USAID in order to support SME enterprises in ICT sector in Vietnam.\r\nMr. Long has extensive experience in business strategy, marketing, sales, business incubation and public relations in ICT industry in Vietnam. He was a holder of a B.S degree in Computer Science from The Hochiminh City Teacher Training Technology University and Master degree in Economics Science from Vietnam National University.',	'Long Lam-Nguyen-Hai',	'',	'inherit',	'open',	'open',	'',	'538-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2015-01-14 10:56:11',	'2015-01-14 10:56:11',	'',	538,	'https://nhunguyen-nhunguyen1980.c9.io/Vnito/538-revision-v1/',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
