(931,	5,	'2015-01-15 11:35:03',	'2015-01-15 11:35:03',	'Cuong La-Manh is the Managing Director of Luxoft Vietnam Company, a subsidiary of the global leading IT Solution &amp; Service Provider Luxoft (NYSE:LXFT US). Cuong is responsible for overall operations and growth of Luxoft global Delivery Center, relationships with key customers and strategic partnerships within Vietnam country.\r\n\r\nCuong has more than 20 years of experience working in the IT and software industry at major Vietnamese and International companies. His deep knowledge of domestic as well as international markets supported by strong hands-on managerial experience greatly contributed to the successful startup and growth of Luxoft in the region.\r\n\r\nCuong holds an Engineer Degree from HCMC University of Agriculture and Forestry, an MBA Degree from Open University Malaysia and has accomplished a number of various international business courses in Software Engineering and Management',	'Cuong La-Manh',	'',	'inherit',	'open',	'open',	'',	'34-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2015-01-15 11:35:03',	'2015-01-15 11:35:03',	'',	34,	'https://nhunguyen-nhunguyen1980.c9.io/Vnito/34-revision-v1/',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
(932,	5,	'2015-01-27 06:36:18',	'2015-01-27 06:36:18',	'Hgraduated from University of Economics in HCM (UEH) city in 1985 and worked as an economic expert in export-import area at a SOE in HCM city. Six years later, moved to the Saigon Jewelry Company (SJC) and appointed to be the Business Manager and Representative of SJC in a Joint Venture entity with Hong Kong. Hai took the Master of Development Economics under Vietnam-the Netherlands program offered at UEH from 1995-1998.\n\nAfter six years working at SJC, Hai moved to Hochiminh Export Processing Zone Authority (HEPZA) and appointed to be a Vice Rector of the College belonged to HEPZA since 1999. Receiving Vietnamese Government Scholarship, Hai went to University of Illinois at Chicago (UIC), USA for Ph.D. study since 2004. Returning home in early 2008 and starting – up the Gold Exchange named VGB, Hai made VGB good value during 2008-2010. In Oct. 2010, Hai took and invested in Viendong College and has built the long-term reputation for Viendong College. Besides teaching at Viendong College, Hai is also a financial expert and regularly appears on such outstanding newspapers as Tuoitre, Thanhnien, HTV, VTV.',	'Hai Tran-Thanh',	'',	'inherit',	'open',	'open',	'',	'519-autosave-v1',	'',	'',	'2015-01-27 06:36:18',	'2015-01-27 06:36:18',	'',	519,	'https://nhunguyen-nhunguyen1980.c9.io/Vnito/519-autosave-v1/',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
(933,	5,	'2015-01-15 11:42:28',	'2015-01-15 11:42:28',	'Mr. Long Lam-Nguyen-Hai (Long Lam) worked as Deputy CEO of Quang Trung Software City (QTSC) which was the biggest information technology park in Vietnam (www.qtsc.com.vn). Prior this role, he led as Project Director, CMO and Head of Business Support Center and Public Relations. Long also charged Vice Chairman of ICT Partnerships Club - the ICT businessmen club in Vietnam with over 80 members.\r\n\r\nAs an information technology industry expert, he was a President of the Asia Oceania Regional Software Park Alliance in the term 2010-2012, a member of consultant board to support Vietnam Software Business Incubator design the business plan and strategy for development in order to report to Vietnamese Government and European Commission. Furthermore, he contributed positively to VNCI project (www.vnci.org) funded by USAID in order to support SME enterprises in ICT sector in Vietnam.\r\n\r\nMr. Long has extensive experience in business strategy, marketing, sales, business incubation and public relations in ICT industry in Vietnam. He was a holder of a B.S degree in Computer Science from The Hochiminh City Teacher Training Technology University and Master degree in Economics Science from Vietnam National University.',	'Long Lam-Nguyen-Hai',	'',	'inherit',	'open',	'open',	'',	'538-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2015-01-15 11:42:28',	'2015-01-15 11:42:28',	'',	538,	'https://nhunguyen-nhunguyen1980.c9.io/Vnito/538-revision-v1/',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
