(972,	1,	'2015-01-21 17:37:14',	'2015-01-21 17:37:14',	'As one of the original co-founders of LARION in 2003, Nhuan provides the visionary guidance that has led to LARION’s outstanding growth and successes in client software development on an international basis.\r\n\r\nWith an impressive and diverse professional portfolio, Nhuan’s expertise covers several industry sectors including Telecommunications, Healthcare and Financial markets across the US, Europe and Asia where he has gained his extensive experience of successfully managing the full lifecycle development of state-of-the-art applications for a number of high profile organisations. Before forming LARION Nhuan served as a key faculty member at NIIT, a leading global talent development corporation. Prior to joining NIIT, he fulfilled the role of Head of Software Development for Arrive Technologies Vietnam (a US high-tech telecommunications start up). Before joining Arrive Technologies Vietnam, Nhuan was Manager of the Software Department for Next Level Communications Vietnam, which was acquired by Motorola.\r\n\r\nNhuan holds a Master’s Degree in IT Engineering from HCMC University of Technology, Vietnam. He is an Executive Member of the Board of Executives for HCA [Ho Chi Minh City Computer Association] and YBAHCM [HCMC Young Businessmen Association]',	'Nhuan Lai-Duc',	'',	'inherit',	'open',	'open',	'',	'24-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2015-01-21 17:37:14',	'2015-01-21 17:37:14',	'',	24,	'https://nhunguyen-nhunguyen1980.c9.io/Vnito/24-revision-v1/',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
(973,	5,	'2015-01-27 09:27:54',	'2015-01-27 09:27:54',	'<strong>Frank Schellenberg</strong> is the founder and shareholder of <strong>DIGI-TEXX</strong> – a successful Business Process Outsourcing Company that has been operating in Vietnam since 2003.\n\nIn 2004, Mr. Schellenberg founded GHP Far East (now known as Swiss Post Solutions) as a spin-off of DIGI-TEXX for the GHP Group from Germany and led the company as CEO until 2014. He made GHP Far East a leading BPO and Software Development provider in Vietnam.\n\nHe supports foreign investors to invest in Vietnam and has also invested in other IT related companies including <strong><em>DSG Vietnam, Travel2Pay, RASIA, Saigon IT Partner</em> </strong>and<strong> <em>BIPS.</em></strong>\n\nSchellenberg now owns a consulting company, <strong><em>Schellenberg Consulting Ltd</em></strong><em>. </em>which provides professional technical, finance and legal support for investors in the IT industry. Additionally, he works actively in advisory committees for universities and international schools.\n\nMr. Schellenberg earned a Master’s degree of Engineering from Friedrich Schiller University Jena in Germany in 1985 and gained his international leadership skills as an IT manager in the publishing and communication industry before he relocated to Vietnam in 2000. He is highly committed to technology and perpetual entrepreneurship.',	'Frank Schellenberg',	'',	'inherit',	'open',	'open',	'',	'431-autosave-v1',	'',	'',	'2015-01-27 09:27:54',	'2015-01-27 09:27:54',	'',	431,	'https://nhunguyen-nhunguyen1980.c9.io/Vnito/431-autosave-v1/',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
