(990,	5,	'2015-01-26 11:55:42',	'2015-01-26 11:55:42',	'<strong>Education:</strong>\r\n\r\n1973-1977: Graduated from Tokyo University of Fisheries, Japan.\r\n(now Tokyo University of Marine and Technology)\r\nB.Sc. in Fishing Science &amp; Technology.\r\n\r\n1982-1884: Graduated from Canberra University, Australia.\r\nGraduated Diploma in Computing Studies.\r\n\r\n1997-1999: Graduated from National University, CA., U.S.A.\r\nMBA in Telecommunication Management.\r\n\r\n<strong>Working Experience:</strong>\r\n\r\n1977-1982: Business Development, Mitsui Ocean Development\r\n&amp; Engineering Co., Ltd. Tokyo. (now MODEC, Inc.)\r\nA joint-venture company between Mitsui &amp; Co., Ltd.\r\nMitsui Shipbuilding Co., Ltd. to build oil drilling\r\nplatform &amp; semi-submersible vessels.\r\n\r\n1984-1990: Senior Programmer/Analyst at Department of\r\nPrimary Industries, Australian government.\r\nDeveloped and maintained systems using COBOL &amp;\r\nIBM 4GL (Speed II) programming language.\r\n\r\n1991-1994: Assistant Manager, Toyota Trading America, Inc.\r\nIn-charge of project coordination between US\r\nengineers and Japanese engineers at Toyota Motor\r\nin Kentucky State, USA.\r\n\r\n1994-1995: Programmer/Analyst for Honda Australia, Melbourne.\r\nDeveloped and maintained systems using COBOL.\r\n\r\n1997-2002: Vice President, Why Not Creation Inc., USA\r\nThis is a start-up company during the dot.com\r\nboom in Silicon Valley. We raised a total of 10\r\nMillion USD to build a web portal providing online\r\ngreeting card services www.ynot.com. Now it’s a part\r\nof www.rakuten.co.jp (online greeting card section)\r\nIn 2000 we had over 200 employees (80 in the US, 80\r\nin Vietnam, 40 in Japan &amp; 10 in France)\r\nI build the subsidiary in Japan (Why Not Co., Ltd.) in\r\n1998 from scratch and later Why Not Japan was\r\nacquired by a well-known internet portal in Japan.\r\n\r\n2002-2008: Chairman &amp; CEO, Sang Tao Corporation, HCM.\r\nSang Tao was founded in 1997 and was pioneer in\r\nproviding ITO services in Vietnam.\r\nSang Tao was the first Vietnamese IT company\r\nacquired by a big Japanese IT company in 2007.\r\n\r\n2012- present: Co-Founder &amp; CEO, LZT Vietnam Co., Ltd.\r\nProviding software outsourcing services and\r\nbusiness strategic consulting services.\r\nLZT group companies has a total of nearly 600\r\nsoftware engineers in China, Japan &amp; Vietnam.',	'Hung Nguyen-Doan',	'',	'publish',	'open',	'open',	'',	'hung-nguyen-doan',	'',	'',	'2015-02-12 03:18:30',	'2015-02-12 03:18:30',	'',	0,	'https://nhunguyen-nhunguyen1980.c9.io/Vnito/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=990',	7,	'speaker',	'',	0),
